22.html|title=Ahimsa |publisher=MMDB|accessdate=2009-07-29}}</ref> The film won [[Kerala State Film Award]] for [[Kerala State Film Award for Second Best Actor|Second Best Actor]] (Mammootty) and [[Kerala State Film Award for Best Editor|Best Editor]] (Narayanan).<ref>[http://www.prd.kerala.gov.in/stateawards2.htm Official Website Of Information And Public Relation Department Of Kerala<!-- Bot generated title -->] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160303234213/http://www.prd.kerala.gov.in/stateawards2.htm |date=3 March 2016 }}</ref>\n\nPlot\n\nThis film tells the story of atrocities in society.\n\n==Cast==\n{{colbegin}}\n*[[Sukumaran]] as  Devan\n*[[Ratheesh]] as  Bharathan\n*[[Poornima Jayaram]] as  Suma\n*[[Menaka (actress)|Menaka]] as Safiya\n*[[Mammootty]] as Vasu\n*[[Mohanlal]] as  Mohan\n*[[Lalu Alex]] as   Raghu\n*[[Jose Prakash]] as  R. K.\n*[[Balan K. Nair]] as  Kunjutty\n*[[Seema (actress)|Seema]] as  Ani\n*[[Jose (Malayalam actor)|Jose]] as  Suresh\n*[[Kuthiravattom Pappu]] as  Muthu\n*[[Achankunju]] as  Kuttayi\n*[[Sukumari]] as  Bharathan's Mother\n*[[Prathapachandran]] as  Govindan\n*[[Sathaar]] as  Bichu\n*[[T. G. Ravi]] as  Peter\n*[[Sreenivasan (actor)|Sreenivasan]] as  Raju\n*[[Swapna (actress)|Swapna]] as  Radha\n*[[K.P.A.C. Sunny]] as  Pappan\n*[[Kunjandi]]\n*[[Kothuku Nanappan]] as  Sankaran\n*[[Kunchan (actor)|Kunchan]] as  Dasan\n*[[Vilasini]] as  Lakshmi\n*[[Rajalakshmi (actress)|Rajalakshmi]]\n{{colend}}\n\n==Soundtrack==\n\nThe soundtrack features four songs, all written by [[Bichu Thirumala]] and composed by [[A. T. Ummer]].\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Song !! Singer(s) !! Lyrics !! Duration\n|-\n| ''Kaattu tharattum''\n| [[K. J. Yesudas]], [[S. Janaki]]\n| [[Bichu Thirumala]]\n|\n|-\n| ''Njanoru dhobhi''\n| K. J. Yesudas\n| Bichu Thirumala\n|\n|-\n| ''Jalasankhu pushpam''\n| S. Janaki\n| Bichu Thirumala\n|\n|-\n| ''Sulthano''\n| [[K. J. Yesudas]], [[S. Janaki]]\n| Bichu Thirumala\n|\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n